Nandipha Mlambo (white top) and Nonhle Zaca (black top) displayed their stickfighting skills during the tourism and heritage event at Underberg south of KZN on Saturday. The ladies said they will use their skills to defend themselves from abuse by men. The event was organized  by Dr Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma municipality as part of indigenous game for men but mayor Ngeneleni Mncwabe said she decided the game be introduced to women as well so that they  use it to defend themselves from abusive men. 